Exomiser

Exomiser is a tool to annotate variants from a vcf file. It takes human phenotype ontology (HPO) terms as input and uses a database of known disease-gene links to score variants. It incorporates information from model organisms to score variants that dont have a human disease association.

Exomiser annotates variants with a human phenotype score and a combined score (model organisms + human)

Dataset

The molecular genetisist wants me to look at this data set to help him show the utility of exomiser over time.

  • A list of rare, final variants.
  • Six different exomiser versions (6-11)
  • Human phenotype score
  • Combined score

There are 731 observations per exomiser version.
